<h4>How to use this app</h4>
<p>
<b>My Game Plan</b> is designed to help people struggling with thoughts of suicide. It can be used in the following way.
<ol>
<li>Complete a <b>safety plan</b> with the help of a doctor or other care provider. In this app you can enter <i>warning signs</i>, <i>coping strategies</i>, and supportive <i>phone contacts</i>. For warning signs and coping strategies, you can choose a suggestion or enter your own.
<li>Enter <b>appointments</b> and set reminders.
<li>Go through the safety plan to identify when you have one of the warning signs. You can mark each time you have it, and app remembers (this information does not leave the privacy of your phone).
<li>Choose a coping strategy. The pre-suggested strategies link to other free mobile apps that specialize in helping with those strategies.
<li>Access your supportive <b>contacts</b> whenever you need to. There is also a button to call the Suicide Prevention Lifeline (United States only).
<li>Browse the <b>resources</b> for important news and tips from the suicide prevention community.
</ol>
</p>


</body>
